  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (2026-Q1 baseline)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Model suite updated to 2026-Q1 baseline incorporating revised impeller geometry tolerances and updated turbulence-model coefficients; regulatory requirement binding retains ASME V&V 40-2018 citation without referencing the 2022 Addendum A corrections to hemolysis-index normalisation guidance.",
